							<h1>Did you know? </h1>
	<h2>The bright green body colour of this organism is due to the presence of chloroplasts inside its cell. 
	Euglena’s chloroplasts are unique because they are surrounded by three membranes. The chloroplasts are known to 
	contain pyrenoids which are used in the synthesis of paramylon, a storage form of starch. The presence of pyrenoids
	is the most distinctive feature of this genus. All Euglenoids possess two flagella rooted in basal bodies.

							<!-- <a href="http://freehtml5.co" target="_blank">FreeHTML5.co</a> --> </h2>
